---
import { fade } from "astro:transitions";
---

<div
	class="relative flex flex-col items-center"
	transition:animate={fade({ duration: "0.25s" })}>
	<h1
		class="relative mx-auto mb-[40px] mt-[100px] inline-block text-center text-2xl font-bold before:absolute before:-bottom-1 before:left-0 before:h-[0.3rem] before:w-full before:rounded-full before:bg-orange-500 sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl">
		About
	</h1>
	<p
		class="w-[85%] text-balance text-center text-base text-neutral-200 sm:w-[80%] sm:text-lg md:w-[70%] lg:w-[50%] lg:text-xl">
		Hello, I&apos;m Jay Patel, a passionate software developer dedicated to
		creating impactful full-stack applications that make a difference. By day, I
		serve as a Software Developer for the United States Air Force, where I bring
		my technical expertise to mission critical projects. In my free time,
		I&apos;m always experimenting with new technologies and building innovative
		applications. Most recently, I&apos;ve been diving into Astro to due to
		it&apos;s performance and suitability for content-rich websites.
	</p>
</div>
